==English==
===Noun===
'''a la mode'''
A software company in the U.S with headquarters in Oklahoma City, OK and satellite offices in Salt Lake City, UT and Orlando FL, which focuses on real estate-related technology.  Founded in 1985, a la mode, inc. is maker of WinTOTAL real estate appraisal software, the most widely used software of its kind in the United States.  The company's "XSites" website product designed for mortgage originators boasts the largest customer base of mortgage professionals of any company that designs websites specifically for the mortgage industry in the U.S. (accurate as of early July, 2006).  The company's website is located at http://www.alamode.com.